  <refnamediv>
    <refname>defvar</refname>
    <refpurpose> define a freefem formal variable in Scilab environment </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>U_out = defvar(U_in)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>U_in</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>a string, a vector or matrix of string giving the name of the components of the formal variable</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>U_out</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>a ffeq data structure (tlist)</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>defvar defines a freefem formal variable in Scilab environment allowing to build PDE formulations.</para>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[ 
u     = defvar(['u1';'u2']);
eps_u = grad(u);
 ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
  
